com.esri.mo2.cs.geom
Interface PointCollection

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, Geometry, GeometryCollection, HitTest, PointApplicatorUser
All Known Subinterfaces:
MPointCollection, MZPointCollection
All Known Implementing Classes:
BasePointsArray, MBasePointsArray, MZBasePointsArray
public interface PointCollection
extends GeometryCollection, HitTest, PointApplicatorUser

A prototypical collection of Points that exist in all Geometry classes and interfaces. Implementation can done using arrays or one of the generic Java collections, for example, java.util.List might be better within an editing environment.

segmentHitTest

public boolean segmentHitTest(Point queryPoint,
                              double searchRadius,
                              SegmentHitResult result,
                              boolean addLastSegment)
Finds the closest segment (in an ordered collection) to a query point. If a hit is found, the contents of SegmentHitResult will be updated, else will be undefined.

Parameters:
queryPoint - the center of the search radius
searchRadius - the maximum distance to consider
result - the start vertex of the segment which is closest the query point
Returns:
a boolean value -True if a hit is found, else False
